{"name":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/nature/root-vine-caduceus-healing.webp","system":{"npcType":"broken_one","oppositionLevel":7,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Margareta Westen is a wealthy noblewoman who was born with a facial deformity. Society rejected her despite her wealth and noble birth, treating her as a monster because of her appearance. Rather than becoming bitter, Margareta used her magic and her fortune to create a haven in the village of Gelb where the rejected could live in peace and dignity. She is the Good Witch of the Yellow Village, holder of the western piece of the Compass Rose. Margareta is genuinely kind and maternal, using emotion manipulation magic to ease the pain of outcasts and telekinesis to provide for their needs. She welcomes the Hunters warmly and explains her mission: to provide a safe haven for those rejected by society. When OZena comes to kill her and steal her Compass Rose piece, Margareta shows compassion even to her would-be assassin—she recognizes that Dorothea is suffering and has been manipulated. Margareta knows that OZena murdered Johanne two weeks ago and understands that Dr. Henkle is the true villain manipulating Dorothea from Smaragd. Her compassion is both her greatest strength and her fatal weakness—she hesitates to harm even those who threaten her. If she survives, she warns the Hunters about Helga in Rot and the danger of the incomplete Compass Rose. If she dies, the village of Gelb falls into despair.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":3,"max":3},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I was born with a facial deformity and society rejected me","I use my magic and fortune to create a haven for outcasts","I ease suffering wherever I can find it","My compassion makes me vulnerable to those who would harm me"],"gifts":[{"name":"Witch - Emotion Manipulation","description":"Margareta can perform a Check to alter the emotional state of anyone she can see. She can make them feel calm, afraid, angry, or loving. This lasts for one Scene. Victims can resist with a Check against her Opposition Level (7). She uses this primarily to ease the pain and shame of outcasts, helping them find peace with their conditions."},{"name":"Witch - Telekinesis","description":"Margareta can move objects with her mind. She can lift and throw items weighing up to 200 pounds. In combat, she can use this to disarm opponents, create barriers from environmental objects, or hurl items as weapons (treating this as a normal attack with her OL). She uses this to provide for her village's needs and defend them when necessary."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Protect my village and the outcasts who live here","Use my magic to ease suffering","Stop OZena before she kills more witches","Guard the western piece of the Compass Rose"],"notes":"Margareta is OZena's second target (Johanne was first). She holds the YELLOW/WEST piece of Compass Rose. She knows: Compass Rose split 4 ways, Johanne murdered, OZena manipulated by Henkle, Henkle in Smaragd. Compassion is weakness—hesitates to harm even attackers. If killed, Gelb falls into despair, outcasts terrified. If survives, warns about Helga in Rot, may give Hunters her Compass piece. Voice: Warm, maternal, slight German accent. Mannerisms: Touches people gently, maintains eye contact despite deformity, smiles kindly. Only 1 Wound but OL 7 makes her formidable with magic."},"_id":"7c6b709c4cd380ad"}
{"name":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/time/clock-face-tan.webp","system":{"npcType":"broken_one","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Dr. Norman Henkle is a brilliant researcher from the early 1900s who was transported to 1780 through mysterious circumstances (orchestrated by the One Who Plots in the Shadows). In this primitive era, his future knowledge makes him appear to be a powerful wizard. He appears as a charming man in his 40s, dressed in anachronistic clothing mixing 1900s and 1780s fashion. He carries himself with absolute confidence and speaks with a silver tongue that has convinced countless people to follow him. When he arrived in Smaragd with his patients (Dorothea, Lowe, Hirnloser, and Dose), he used his knowledge of penicillin (150 years before its actual discovery) to cure an epidemic, and the grateful villagers made him their leader. He discovered the magical wishing well and learned to manipulate it, transforming Smaragd into his fortress. He manipulated Dorothea into murdering the other witches to collect Compass Rose pieces, planning to use the incomplete artifact to escape—either returning to his time as a powerful wizard or conquering both eras. His genius is mostly stolen—surface knowledge of many subjects but deep understanding of none. He's a master manipulator but completely amoral, seeing everyone (including his patients) as tools. His ultimate plan is to activate the Compass Rose while in his hot-air balloon, believing he can control his destination. He doesn't care that the incomplete artifact will tear reality and throw people randomly through time.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":2,"max":2},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a brilliant researcher from 1900s, appearing as a wizard in 1780","My future knowledge makes me a god among primitives","I will escape this era at any cost","Everyone is a tool to be used and discarded"],"gifts":[{"name":"Hot-Air Balloon","description":"Henkle has constructed a hot-air balloon using future knowledge as his escape vehicle. **Time Tokens:** During the Scenario, place 1 Time Token on this Gift each time: a combat encounter occurs in Smaragd (max 1 per Scene), Hunters waste time lost in the Labyrinth, or Henkle successfully delays/distracts Hunters. **Ready to Launch:** When 3 Time Tokens accumulate, the balloon is fully inflated and ready. Henkle can board and launch as a single action. **Escape:** Once airborne, extremely difficult to stop—requires creative methods (shooting balloon, magic, climbing tether). If he escapes, activates Compass Rose while airborne."},{"name":"Silver Tongue","description":"Henkle is a master manipulator who has convinced entire villages to follow him. **Deception Mastery:** When attempting to deceive, persuade, or manipulate, his Opposition Level increases by +2 (becomes 7). **NPC Vulnerability:** Any NPC who isn't a Hunter must make a Check against OL 7 to resist believing his lies. He's particularly effective at finding what people want and promising it. **Weakness - Plagiarist:** His genius is mostly stolen. If confronted by someone with true expertise in a topic he's claiming mastery of, his façade crumbles and his OL drops to 3 for that Exchange."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Activate the Compass Rose and escape this primitive era","Protect my stolen research and knowledge","Eliminate anyone who threatens my plans","Maintain my image as a benevolent wizard until I can escape"],"notes":"Henkle doesn't want to fight—he wants to escape. He offers deals constantly: join him, let him go, trade a cure for passage. His primary goal is buying time for the balloon to launch (track Time Tokens). If cornered, becomes desperate and vicious, all charm vanishing. He attempts suicide rather than face capture. Voice: Smooth, charming, American accent. Mannerisms: Constantly smiling (doesn't reach eyes), grand gestures, touches people to establish connection, checks escape routes constantly. If defeated, his research on time travel and the wishing well is incredibly valuable to the Order."},"_id":"fd77cdbf1b1947c9"}
{"name":"Helga - The Red Witch","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/blood/drops-drip-sprinkle-red.webp","system":{"npcType":"broken_one","oppositionLevel":7,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Helga is a blood witch, centuries old but kept young by her dark magic. She appears as a striking woman in her 40s with long red hair and eyes that seem to glow with inner fire. She wears elaborate red robes and is always covered in blood—whether her own or others' is unclear. Helga guards the southern piece of the Compass Rose and rules the village of Rot through blood magic, maintaining a cult of mind-controlled servants. She started centuries ago as a guardian like Margareta, sworn to protect her piece of the Rose, but was corrupted by the power of blood magic. Now she's a tyrant who takes blood willingly given or forcibly taken to sustain her unnatural life. When OZena attempted to infiltrate Rot and steal the Compass piece, Helga captured her and prepared a blood sacrifice ritual for the next full moon. Helga sees herself as dispensing justice—OZena murdered Johanne and Margareta, so she must pay in blood. But Helga's centuries of cruelty have made her more monster than guardian. She can control blood itself, making wounds bleed more, turning blood into weapons, and even taking control of anyone with an open wound. If killed, she drains blood from nearby sources to regenerate, visibly aging each time. Her greatest weakness is the complete Infusion of Purity with elderberry—it negates her blood magic for one Scene, revealing her true ancient age.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":3,"max":3},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a blood witch, centuries old but kept young by magic","I guard the southern piece of the Compass Rose","I punish those who threaten my domain","My power comes from blood willingly given—or forcibly taken"],"gifts":[{"name":"Blood Magic","description":"Helga is a master of blood magic with three primary abilities. **Blood Control:** Can manipulate any blood she can see—make wounds bleed more profusely (inflict 1 additional Wound), turn spilled blood into sharp projectiles, or create barriers of hardened blood. **Blood Puppet:** Once per Scene, take control of any creature with an open wound within 30 feet. Victim must make a Check against her OL to resist; if they fail, they're under her control for one Exchange. **Blood Healing:** Drain blood from nearby sources (servants, animals, pooled blood) to heal herself, restoring 1 Wound by completely draining one human servant."},{"name":"Blood Witch","description":"Helga has sustained her life for centuries through blood magic. When she would be reduced to 0 Wounds, she instead: drains blood from all nearby sources, regenerates 1 Wound immediately, ages visibly (gains wrinkles, gray hair, etc.), and can do this once per Scene. When killed permanently, Helga rapidly ages centuries in moments, crumbling to dust. **Vulnerability:** The complete Infusion of Purity (with elderberry) negates all blood magic for one Scene when splashed on her. Without her magic, she's just an ordinary (very old) woman."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Protect my piece of the Compass Rose","Maintain my cult and power base","Punish OZena for murdering my sister witches","Stay young and powerful forever"],"notes":"Helga won't negotiate unless: (1) the Hunters have evidence of Henkle's manipulation, (2) they use the Infusion of Purity to break her blood magic, or (3) they appeal to her original purpose as a guardian. If combat begins, she's incredibly powerful—controlling blood, taking over wounded opponents, and regenerating when killed. If her magic fails, she ages rapidly into a withered old woman. If spared and freed from blood magic's corruption, she may reveal important truths about Henkle's plans in Smaragd and the true purpose of the Compass Rose. Voice: Commanding and imperious with an ancient accent. Mannerisms: Gestures dramatically, blood swirls around her when angry."},"_id":"b785d0d07c59c682"}